Moreover, the rising emphasis on environmental conservation and biodiversity preservation is driving the adoption of DNA sequencing in ecological studies and wildlife conservation efforts. By exploring the genetic diversity of various species, researchers can gain insights into evolutionary patterns, ecosystem dynamics, and species interactions. This application of sequencing technologies in environmental research underscores the multidisciplinary nature of genomics and its potential to address pressing global challenges.

